Often it’s Often we have to choose between things that are all important to Often the planet But we keep trying each day to be Mason’s engineering background combined with Jess’ endless curiosity and their passion for doing the right things lead to some really fun and meaningful adventures that we wanna share with We’ve worked in Sustainability our whole careers but still have a ton to We love to party and socialize and it’s so hard to think about the planet during those Let’s have fun together and not judge each other if we’re using plastic straws just this We two wonderful kids and sometimes we get those juice boxes cause that’s what’s But we try to raise them thinking about the planet, We’re constantly trying to learn about healthy habits and keep our bodies in good shape even while wrecking them at the bar We want to be good partners and have an awesome sex What’s really in lube, anyways? Please share! Are you an expert on these things? Please reach out and let’s figure out how to megaphone your Things We’re Really, Really Into Health & Wellness, especially Clean Eating – A person with their health has 1,000 dreams, a person without theirs has only We can’t protect the planet without first attending to And health is about % Every year a new study comes out debunking a prior study about what’s good for you and what’s We’ll try to make sense of the data & weigh the benefits against the costs of the latest Mason also kinda wants to live forever, or at least We’ve learned a lot about how the body works and ages, we’ve got a lot more to Home Sustainability – There are almost 8 billion people on the planet & over 1 billion The choices we make in our homes have a profound affect on the the environment around us from how we handle the air we breathe to the water we drink, household waste, energy…it’s all connected! We’re trying to sort through what matters most and help your house be the belle of the ball (that’s a good thing)! Conservation – Humans are easily a major geological event , ushering in a new age called the We’ve moved more earth than some plate tectonic events, we’ve altered the climate more than some solar events, and we’ve kicked off the mass extinction event of the While it often makes is just want to look away, there are lots of small and large things we can do to help the more sensitive organisms out there just survive the human condition (unlike the tardigrade , who needs no help). Residential Land Acreage Income Commercial View All Listings Area About Agents Facebook Contact Area SISKIYOU COUNTY, NORTHERN CALIFORNIA Siskiyou County was incorporated on March , and is located on the west coast of the United States of It is one of the northern most counties in California sharing its northern border with the state of The most spectacular landmark in Siskiyou County is majestic, Mount Shasta which towers ,162 in Siskiyou County is also home to the Klamath Wildlife Refuge, the Marble Mountains Wilderness area, the Sacramento River, McCloud Reservoir, Lake Siskiyou, Lake Shastina, numerous small fishing lakes and streams, the Shasta Trinity National Forest and a variety of mountains, valleys and friendly small Siskiyou County is the fifth largest (in area) county in California and has a population of approximately HISTORY Siskiyou County is home to several Indian tribes including the Shasta, Karuk, Klamath, Modoc, and Wintu In the ’s European fur trappers came to this Gold was discovered in Siskiyou County in the ’s bringing diversified cultures to Siskiyou Ranchers and farmers began settling north of Shasta in what is known as Shasta Settlers moved into every part of the county during this era, displacing the Native Siskiyou County made world headlines during the Modoc War of – when a small group of Modoc Indians held off the US Army in the area near Tulelake, now known as the Lava Beds National Monument and Captain Jack’s Even though the Modocs were greatly outnumbered, it took the army more than a year to overtake Around , with the coming of the railroad, Siskiyou County’s logging industry Saw mills and tent camps could be found in many areas, especially north around Tennant and the area east of McCloud which locals today refer to as McCloud The towns of Tenant and McCloud, Shasta and Weed became full logging Dunsmuir grew as a railroad Yreka remained known for its gold mining Today, after declining years in the logging industry, the local communities attract tourism and outdoor enthusiasts who appreciate and enjoy our pristine scenic The Siskiyou County region offers clean mountain air and water along with outstanding recreational activities including skiing on the snowy mountains, fishing and swimming in the rivers and lakes and hiking and climbing in our spectacular wilderness We invite you to come and see us soon! Liberated Problem Solvers Resources Career Conversations Experiences Donations Join Our Community Meet Our Team About Us Our Mission & Vision Liberated adults are not defined by their economic The philosophy of Liberated Success embraces that every student’s pathway to their economic freedom is complicated and Liberated Success unapologetically endeavors to equip Black, Indigenous, and People of Color students – years of age with the tools that they need, to make educated decisions, that will enable them to enjoy the , joy, peace, and happiness which they Through workforce development and intentional career exploration activities, young people will have the necessary tools and support to make liberated career Our Theory of Change The four prongs of our theory of change are leadership development, career exploration experiences, career counseling, and Internships provide students with experiential learning opportunities to apply what they learn in the classroom to work Liberated Success expands upon the internship model by: Leveraging our community relationships to create opportunities for our students to participate in career exploration experiences with industry mentors Leadership development and career counseling (two essential tools in providing students with the language and knowledge to make a liberated career choice) Developing our students’ social capital to create a network of professional mentors to springboard their careers and aid in providing a foundation for more opportunities down the road Compensating our students for their talents and their participation in internship

UK Becomes First Country in the World to Make Disclosure Mandatory - ESG Today TRENDING: Biden Promises to Rejoin Paris Agreement On First Day Chile Launches Sustainable Bond Framework UK Becomes First Country in the World to Make ESG News Companies Investors Environment Social & Governance Regulators Sustainable Finance Platforms & Markets ESG Q&A About us About us Our Team Advertise with us Select Page UK Becomes First Country in the World to Make Disclosure Mandatory Posted by Mark Segal | Nov 9, | Energy Transition , ESG Reporting , Government , Sustainable Finance | 1 | UK’s Chancellor of the Exchequer Rishi Sunak today made several significant sustainable finance announcements today, including making the UK the first country in the world to mandate economy wide disclosures in line with the Task Force on Financial Disclosures (TCFD). The Chancellor also stated that the UK will issue its first ever sovereign green bond, and will implement a green The new commitments were outlined as part of the UK’s plans to “bolster the dynamism, openness and competitiveness” of the financial services sector, following the country’s departure from the While many companies have ramped efforts to operate more sustainably in recent years, and investors have increasingly pursued ESG integration in their investment , many often report that one of the greatest obstacles to these initiatives remains the lack of consistent, reliable data to know where to target efforts and to measure, analyze and track The TCFD was established to help address these The TCFD was established by the Financial Stability Board in , with the goal of developing consistent disclosure standards for companies, in order to enable investors and other stakeholders to assess the companies’ financial The recommendations were published in June The Chancellor announced that the UK expects to go beyond the “comply or explain” approach, aiming for mandatory disclosures across and financial sectors of the UK economy by , with a significant portion of mandatory requirements in place by According to Chancellor Sunak, the sovereign green bond will be used to help enable the UK meet its net zero target and other environmental objectives, by financing projects that will tackle climate change and infrastructure investments, and creating green jobs across the The green bond is expected to be followed up with a series of further issuances to meet growing investor demand for these Several investors have been calling upon the UK government to participate in the sustainable finance market, including the Green + Gilt proposal launched last month by a group of asset managers and investor groups, representing £10 trillion in assets, urging the issuance of a sovereign green bond to finance the country’s green recovery The UK green taxonomy will be designed to provide a common framework for determining which activities can be defined as environmentally sustainable, aiming to improve understanding of the impact of firms’ activities and investments on the environment and support the transition to a sustainable The UK taxonomy will take the scientific metrics in the EU taxonomy as its Chancellor Sunak said: “We are starting a new chapter in the history of financial services and renewing the UK’s position as the world’s financial By taking as many equivalence decisions as we can in the absence of clarity from the EU, we’re doing what’s right for the UK and providing firms with certainty and “Our plans will ensure the UK moves forward as an open, attractive and market, and continues to lead the world in pioneering new technologies and shifting finance towards a net zero ” Investors and sustainable investing organizations welcomed the announcement of the move to Tan, Global Head of Stewardship and Sustainable Investing, Fidelity International said: “We welcome the Chancellor’s decision for British companies to report in line with the Task Force on Financial Disclosures (TCFD) by Open, honest, consistent and transparent disclosure is a fundamental precondition for the realignment of finance and The TCFD provides an essential platform for asset managers and companies alike to deliver ” Paul Simpson, CEO of focused organization CDP said: “We very much welcome the UK government’s announcement that it will mandate climate disclosure in alignment with the Taskforce on Financial Disclosure (TCFD) As the first G20 government to do so, this sends a powerful signal to the market and other governments that they should follow the UK’s approach, ahead of We look forward to reviewing the scope of these proposed changes: it will be important that they cover all sections of the “This year more than 9,600 companies, representing greater than % global market capitalisation disclosed on climate change through CDP’s disclosure platform, including % of the “Mandating climate disclosure in alignment with the TCFD recommendations will increase the critical mass of data needed by investors and other Functional Medicine Chronic disease is Conventional medicine can’t stop it, but Functional Medicine Functional Medicine is a different approach to care, one that addresses the root cause of an illness instead of relying on drugs to suppress It corrects the mismatch between our bodies and our environment through diet and lifestyle Functional Medicine is the future of healthcare, and it’s our best weapon against chronic How It Works Ancestral Health For Practitioners The Functional Medicine Approach: How (And Why) It Works Chronic disease is climbing in the United States at an alarming Six out of adults have a chronic disease, and four in have two or more Our life expectancy has dropped — for the third year in a row —and heart disease and cancer are the leading causes of death in the The global cost of treating chronic illnesses is projected to reach $47 trillion by the year , unless something can be done to stop this That’s where Functional Medicine comes Functional Medicine is a holistic, , collaborative approach to By using ancestral health strategies to align our bodies more closely with our environment, it shifts the focus away from treating illnesses as they occur to preventing them from developing in the first The Functional Medicine approach deals directly with the underlying cause of a health issue and treats each patient as a whole, unique Practitioners work together with health coaches, nutritionists, and other allied health providers to support patients as they make their journey toward While the Functional Medicine approach is all about preventing or reversing chronic illnesses, the conventional approach focuses on disease management . Rather than encouraging true health, conventional practitioners simply diagnose an illness and try to suppress the symptoms with prescription Those drugs seldom address the root cause of the Instead, they mask symptoms and sometimes even suppress vital bodily functions, leading to unintended side effects—and additional prescriptions to deal with That medication treadmill effectively creates patients for life, and it never solves the underlying cause of the illness . Here’s how it typically works in conventional healthcare: A person with high blood pressure, for example, would sit through a appointment with a doctor and leave with a prescription for a new After that, she’s on her own until her next A Functional Medicine practitioner would instead take the time to uncover what was causing the problem before determining which diet, lifestyle, and environmental interventions would address Then, he would develop an individualized treatment plan together with health coaches and other trained professionals to support their patient as she takes steps to improve her cardiovascular That approach leads to profound, results for patients—and greater satisfaction for Ready to learn more about how the Functional Medicine approach works? Check out the resources How the Functional Medicine Approach Can Prevent or Reverse Chronic Disease The Functional Medicine Approach The Functional Medicine approach is collaborative, holistic, and focused on truly healing patients, not masking symptoms of a chronic Learn more about why it’s different from the conventional approach to Read More about the Unconventional Approach to Medicine Unconventional Medicine Functional Medicine is the key to reinventing healthcare, reversing chronic disease, and building a medical practice you Find out why—and join the Back to Top Why Ancestral Health Is the Solution for the Chronic Disease Problem Why are so many of us suffering from chronic illnesses? Put simply, there’s a mismatch between our bodies and our environment . All organisms on Earth are adapted to live in a specific A mismatch occurs when that environment changes dramatically—and the organism has no time to In humans, that mismatch between our genes and our modern lives is the primary reason why chronic disease has become the monumental problem it is today . To solve that problem, we need to correct the mismatch through ancestral health . What is an Bitcoin xPub (Extended Public Key?) To achieve maximum Bitcoin privacy, Poof generates new bitcoin and cryptocurrency addresses every time funds are Each BTC public address your wallet generates comes from your wallet s xPub (Extended Public Key). Benefits: Poof does not need your private keys Bitcoin and Cryptocurrency payments go directly to your wallet New addresses enhance your Poof also supports yPub and zPub formats and convert them to xPub How to Find xPub On Exodus Wallet? Exodus wallet does not allow you to customize the limit that they track, making it not a recommended way to track or accept Bitcoin To prevent performance issues, Exodus limits the amount (20 max) of addresses without balance that they track on the blockchain for the time While Exodus does not give you customization of address , Poof can still generate payments sent directly to your wallet with Here s how you can Find the xPub on Exodus Wallet: Open up Exodus Bitcoin Wallet on your Click the three small dots on the top right hand of your Click on those dots and you should see the option to “Export xPub”. You should receive a message that says “Your xPub has successfully been exported” along with the file path that points to where your xpub was exported Copy Paste that string of Text into Poof Poof! Una LLC (Limited Liability Company) es un vehículo comercial que le va a permitir clasificar su negocio como una entidad separada personalmente de Esto le va a permitir mantener sus activos personales separados de los activos de la compañía y protegerlos de las deudas y obligaciones de la Con las LLC, puede abrir cuentas bancarias, firmar contratos, contratar empleados, obtener licencias y permisos e incluso comenzar un negocio comercial en los Estados Unidos de En QuickStart le ofrecemos un servicio integral para que usted pueda crear su compañía en los Estados Unidos de América, sin tener que salir de su Florida $750 Búsqueda del nombre de la empresa Tasas Estatales de Creación de la LLC Operating Agreement Standard Servicios de Registered Agent Documento de Constitución Tax identification Number (EIN) Apoyo por email y teléfono Todo el proceso se hace en línea ​ Start now New Mexico $59 monthly Búsqueda del nombre de la empresa Tasas Estatales de Creación de la LLC Operating Agreement Standard Servicios permanente de Registered Agent Documento de Constitución Tax identification Number (EIN) Apoyo por email y teléfono Todo el proceso se hace en línea Elaboración y presentación de Reportes anuales al Estado ​ Start now Wyoming $650 Búsqueda del nombre de la empresa Tasas Estatales de Creación de la LLC Operating Agreement Standard Servicios de Registered Agent Documento de Constitución Tax identification Number (EIN) Apoyo por email y teléfono Todo el proceso se hace en línea ​ Start now ¿Desea crear su compañía en otro estado? Start now Ventajas de Crear una LLC en los Estados Unidos de América 1 ​ Flexibilidad No poseen restricciones en cuanto al número de miembros No tienes que ser Residente (Green Card) ni Ciudadano El Operating agreement (Acuerdo de Socios) decide de qué manera el negocio será 3 Excepción de impuestos para extranjeros Los extranjeros dueños de una LLC pueden estar exentos de pagar impuestos en En caso de que la LLC, (i) no tengan ningún tipo de actividades en USA (tener una cuenta bancaria es USA no es considerado tener actividades) y (ii) ninguno de sus Socios (Miembros) sea un residente fiscal americano, la LLC y sus Socios podrían están exentos del pago de impuestos en 5 Responsabilidad La responsabilidad de los miembros de la LLC se limita generalmente a los activos que cada miembro haya invertido 2 Impuestos Las LLC disfrutan de un solo nivel de tributación (pass through taxation), donde los miembros reportan y pagan su participación en las ganancias y perdidas de la LLC en sus declaraciones de impuestos individuales, es decir, no se paga impuesto a nivel de la Sin embargo, la LLC tiene que presentar su declaración de impuestos (sin pagar). 4 Manejo Las LLC pueden ser manejadas directamente por sus miembros (Member-Managed) o por Managers (Manager-Managed). Estas personas tendrán la facultad de manejar las operaciones del día a día de la 6 Apertura de cuentas bancarias Tener una LLC le va a permitir abrir una cuenta corporativa para que administres los fondos de su Start now QuickStart LLC Contáctanos Dirección: Central Park Square, Suite #2 Los Alamos NM USA Teléfono : +1 (305) Email: Inicio Nosotros Servicios LLC Registered Agent Tax ID ITIN Number Certificate of Good Standing Cuenta de Amazon Seller Contáctanos Legal Legal disclaimer Privacy policy Tarjeta de regalo Otros Servicios More Use tab to navigate through the menu QuickStart LLC ©   QuickStart | Crea tu LLC en USA Inicio Nosotros Servicios LLC Registered Agent Tax ID ITIN Number Certificate of Good Standing Cuenta de Amazon Seller Contáctanos Legal Legal disclaimer Privacy policy Tarjeta de regalo Otros Servicios Use tab to navigate through the menu QuickStart LLC Start now Iniciar sesión ITIN Number Un Número de Identificación Personal del Contribuyente (ITIN), es un número tributario procesador otorgado por el Servicio de Impuestos Internos (IRS). El IRS otorga los ITIN a individuos quienes requieren un número de identificación para fines tributarios en los Estados Unidos pero no tienen ni son elegibles para obtener un Número de Seguro Social (SSN). Los ITIN se emiten sin importar el estado migratorio porque tanto residentes como extranjeros pudieran tener obligaciones tributarias de presentar declaraciones y pagos de impuestos de acuerdo al Código Tributario del Contrata ahora QuickStart LLC Contáctanos Dirección: Central Park Square, Suite #2 Los Alamos NM USA Teléfono : +1 (305) Email: Inicio Nosotros Servicios LLC Registered Agent Tax ID ITIN Number Certificate of Good Standing Cuenta de Amazon Seller Contáctanos Legal Legal disclaimer Privacy policy Tarjet

Posted on Jul 1, Co-president Taylor Park recently finished a marine mammal rehabilitation and research lab program at Pacific Marine Mammal Center located in Laguna Beach and learned about the toxic algae bloom that is hurting our marine mammal She asks to be mindful not to touch or Read More View All Social Impact Leadership & Outreach Dynamite Book Club is a youth service project in Orange County, CA working with local nonprofits and government agency partnerships to build a better community through Purpose: Inspired by BTS s song, "Dynamite", Dynamite Book Club was established in November of and was created in response to the negative impact of the pandemic bringing positivity to the youth in our local communities by addressing facilitating the needs of the underserved and general public (i.e., library closures, access to basic needs resources, career questions, teens’ mental health), while also introducing teens to new student learning opportunities and a wide range of career pathways through experiences, opening up the minds of students through connections, networks, and friends, finding their purpose in As of Dynamite Book Club ( Taylor Park, Layla Hahn, Shuyi "Susan" Zhang, & Alexandra Law ), our initial vision & mission was to bring literacy access to the underserved communities in Santa Ana through little free libraries and book Little did we know that our vision & mission would evolve into a greater journey with plus teen, young adult, and parent volunteers across Orange We started with a Founding Team ( Carter Park, Addison Briggeman, Mackenzie Lee, & Ayla Kailiponi) , who started with the installation of Little Free Library nonprofit charters (113111, ) in Santa Ana businesses, then expanded into the City of Garden Grove launching a library at Buena Clinton Youth & Family Center (City-run community center). The community service projects led our youth service club to work with new community partnerships, serving with local nonprofits and County & City government With a network of + student volunteers across Orange County, we focus on supporting local nonprofits and government leaders in community service projects, community event volunteer support, and basic needs assistance while also providing teens, young adults, and their families a variety of service opportunities to learn about the greater community as well as student leadership Dynamite Book Club Little Library Projects: We have brought little libraries to the greater community across the City of Santa Ana (i.e., The Santa Ana Zoo, The Blue Lot, Libro Mobile s Bicycle Library stewardship, Mabury Park neighborhood, La Purisima Naturista, Bristol Food Court, Bristol Swap Mall), Rossmoor District (Rush Park ), and Thomas House Family Shelter (Garden Grove) with pending library projects to be Please let us know if you would like one in your organization, business, or neighborhood! Event Volunteering: We volunteer with nonprofits & government leaders, serving at in community & cultural events, grocery distributions, resource fairs, and neighborhood beautification promoting literacy, arts, & culture, healthcare vaccination outreach, and basic need

on Growth Assets Five Keys to Managing Remote Sales Teams by Stephen Diorio June , 7 minute read 1 Shares 1 0 0 0 The coronavirus pandemic has forced billions of people worldwide to remain at home – displacing selling teams and accelerating the adoption of virtual selling channels . Few organizations were prepared for this scale of employee % of sales leaders report their businesses will be disrupted by the pandemic by over five sales quarters as they adapt to uncertainty, changing buyer behavior, and new ways of working according to research by the Revenue Enablement Institute . Sales productivity has dropped by % since the pandemic started as executives struggle to adapt to managing and measuring remote salespeople, call center representatives, and customer support And most executives believe the changes brought on by the pandemic will transform the way they sell Sales leaders are now being forced to quickly adapt their commercial models to this new buying reality by: Transitioning from “old school” selling to virtual selling approaches better suited to the demands of “new school” buyers who prefer to work through digital channels Building “digital first” sales infrastructure to support remote selling at scale And getting much more leverage, visibility, customer engagement, and speed from “The global spread of the coronavirus is the tipping point for virtual selling, which represents the commercial model of the future,” reports Michael Smith, a Managing Director at Blue Ridge Partners who has helped over businesses improve their selling “Looking past the pandemic, the coronavirus response has pushed most sales organizations past the point of no return where the adoption rate of remote selling channels and “new school” digital buying practices will transform selling as we know This will redefine the commercial model by accelerating the cadence of sales, forcing higher levels of digital engagement, and introducing entirely new sales management ”. Bob Kelly, Chairman of the Sales Management Association (SMA) which the Remote Sales Productivity Report, anticipates the pressure to respond to the coronavirus will finally give sales leaders the shove they need to become adaptable, , and learning agile . “The response to the coronavirus crisis has created a “shoving point” that will force sales managers to truly rely on technology or be left That shove will send many But I ultimately believe most sales forces, or their managers will rise to the challenge and adapt to challenging markets, re organize with heightened purpose, and remake their organizations in a more remote selling ” Unfortunately, sales leaders have limited time or resources to make this This raises the stakes on the difficult resource allocation and investment decisions they must make in the coming With planning for the fiscal year just months away, the vast majority (98%) of organizations will have no additional funds to make these In fact, two thirds have had to cut their sales budgets in response to s
